for like a week

06:12.693 --> 06:14.492
when she finds out
I bombed this test.

06:14.494 --> 06:15.928
Doesn't your sister
get straight As?

06:15.930 --> 06:17.129
Half-sister.

06:17.131 --> 06:19.465
Grades aren't hereditary,
Nicole.

06:19.467 --> 06:20.499
Whatever.

06:41.190 --> 06:42.191
Hey, Ads.

06:43.192 --> 06:44.159
Hey, Dorian.

06:45.661 --> 06:46.827
Ads?

06:46.829 --> 06:47.897
Stop!

06:49.965 --> 06:52.733
So what are you and your dad
gonna do this weekend?

06:52.735 --> 06:54.568
I don't know.
He got a new apartment,

06:54.570 --> 06:56.204
so we're probably
just gonna hang out there.

06:56.206 --> 06:58.773
And he also says
he has a surprise for me. So...

06:58.775 --> 07:00.507
When's the last time
you saw him?

07:00.509 --> 07:02.175
Um, it's been a while.

07:02.177 --> 07:04.212
I talked to him last weekend
and his band was like opening up

07:04.214 --> 07:05.913
for a band
I've never heard of.

07:05.915 --> 07:08.283
I wish my dad was a singer
in a band.

07:08.285 --> 07:10.718
Tell my mom that and all
she does is complain about him.

07:10.720 --> 07:12.220
Well,
I think your dad's cool.

07:12.222 --> 07:14.390
I mean I love my dad,
but he's an accountant

07:14.392 --> 07:15.823
and that's pretty lame.

07:15.825 --> 07:18.426
- Alright, bye. See you Monday.
- Bye, see you.

07:18.428 --> 07:20.828
So how was your math test?

07:20.830 --> 07:23.065
Ugh, you know.

07:23.067 --> 07:24.732
That bad, huh?

07:24.734 --> 07:26.433
Hopefully, it's fine.

07:26.435 --> 07:27.769
How was your diorama?

07:27.771 --> 07:29.570
It was good.

07:29.572 --> 07:30.772
Good?

07:30.774 --> 07:32.540
Just good?
I thought it was pretty lit.

07:32.542 --> 07:35.311
Thanks.
I spent all week on it.

07:35.313 --> 07:37.112
Is your dad coming tonight?

07:37.114 --> 07:39.048
Yes. Yeah, he is.

07:39.050 --> 07:41.450
Cool. I like your dad.
He's the best.

07:41.452 --> 07:42.985
<i>In sports, the International...</i>

07:42.987 --> 07:44.421
High five.

07:44.423 --> 07:45.921
Oh, sorry, yeah.

07:45.923 --> 07:48.290
Right there, good girl!

07:48.292 --> 07:49.792
Here.

07:52.462 --> 07:53.564
Hey!

08:00.805 --> 08:02.738
There is my princess.

08:02.740 --> 08:05.241
- Hi, Dad.
- Oh, I've missed you.

08:05.243 --> 08:06.475
I missed you, too.

08:06.477 --> 08:07.510
How was tour?

08:07.512 --> 08:09.913
Hey, the tour was a blast.

08:09.915 --> 08:12.915
Five bands,
and the crowds were great,

08:12.917 --> 08:14.583
and they liked us so...

08:14.585 --> 08:15.885
Well, yeah, I play your songs

08:15.887 --> 08:17.653
to my friends all the time
and we love it.

08:17.655 --> 08:19.555
Oh,
that's what I like to hear.

08:19.557 --> 08:20.824
Hey there, Gwendolyn.

08:20.826 --> 08:22.959
- You're looking good.
- Thank you, Robert.

08:22.961 --> 08:24.928
Oh, big James!

08:24.930 --> 08:26.830
- Good to see you, buddy.
- Yeah, you, too.

08:26.832 --> 08:29.433
You, too. Looks like tour life
is treating you well.

08:29.435 --> 08:31.002
- Well, I can't complain.
- Yeah.

08:31.004 --> 08:31.904
I bet.

08:33.139 --> 08:34.472
And Miss Ella,
how are you?

08:34.475 --> 08:36.606
I'm great. Have you met Dally?

08:36.607 --> 08:39.143
I believe I have,
but hello again, Dally.

08:39.145 --> 08:41.778
Oh, I got you guys somethin'.

08:41.780 --> 08:44.782
Um,
thought you might like these.

08:44.784 --> 08:47.985
- Signed by Coral herself.
- You know Coral?

08:47.987 --> 08:49.520
Yeah,
we've been on tour together.

08:49.522 --> 08:52.290
- Sure, I know Coral.
- Dad, this is so cool.

08:52.292 --> 08:54.159
Seriously, Robert,
thank you.

08:54.161 --> 08:55.994
- Anytime. My pleasure.
- Hey.

08:55.996 --> 08:57.528
Uh, can we offer you a drink?

08:57.530 --> 09:00.998
We've got um, apple juice.

09:01.000 --> 09:02.666
Actually,
we should get goin'.

09:02.668 --> 09:04.869
I have a surprise
for my little princess

09:04.871 --> 09:06.871
and I don't want us
to be late. So...

09:06.873 --> 09:09.174
Are you taking me somewhere
for the weekend?

09:09.176 --> 09:10.976
Uh, about the weekend...

09:10.978 --> 09:13.979
Oh boy, here we go again.
What is it this time, Robert?

09:13.981 --> 09:16.148
Mom! Let Dad talk.

09:16.150 --> 09:19.519
I have a three-day festival
that I have to go do,

09:19.521 --> 09:21.954
but I swear
I'll be back Tuesday,

09:21.956 --> 09:24.189
and I'll come pick you up,
and you can stay with me

09:24.191 --> 09:25.556
till I go back on tour.

09:25.558 --> 09:27.325
Okay, yeah, that's fine,
that's great.

09:27.327 --> 09:29.961
Robert, why don't you and I have
a little chat outside?

09:29.963 --> 09:31.364
Mom?

09:31.366 --> 09:32.532
Addy.

09:32.534 --> 09:33.834
It's okay, baby.

09:44.245 --> 09:45.578
What is it?

09:45.580 --> 09:47.679
When are you gonna stop
doing this to her?

09:47.681 --> 09:49.916
I've got one more gig
and I'll be set.

09:49.918 --> 09:52.185
We'll have plenty
of time together after that.

09:52.187 --> 09:54.387
It's always one more gig
with you, Robert.

09:54.389 --> 09:57.090
- It's exactly why we didn't work out.
- Oh!

09:57.092 --> 09:59.226
I got over you
not being a good husband,

09:59.228 --> 10:01.228
I don't know how she's
gonna be able to get over you

10:01.230 --> 10:02.264
not being a good dad.

10:05.367 --> 10:07.303
I'm doing the best I can,
Gwen.

10:13.741 --> 10:15.077
Let's go, princess.

10:21.016 --> 10:21.917
Hug.

10:23.752 --> 10:25.752
We won't be late,
I promise.

10:25.754 --> 10:26.956
Right.
See you later.

